gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Spurs 126, Warriors 113
gameRecap.excerpt: San Antonio defeats Golden State, 126-113. For San Antonio, Keldon Johnson led the way with 22 points (4 3PM) and 11 rebounds while aided by Malaki Branham (20 points, three rebounds) and Jeremy Sochan (20 points, five rebounds) in the victory. Klay Thompson finished with 27 points (five 3PM) with Jonathan Kuminga tallying 26 points and three rebounds for Golden State in the losing effort. San Antonio improves to 14-50, while Golden State moves to 33-30 in the loss.
